The paper deals with iterative algorithms for solving the generalized eigenvector problem and canonical correlation analysis, which are fundamental problems in data analysis and scientific computing with numerous applications in machine learning and statistics. The paper also focuses on improving the runtimes of these algorithms for large-scale matrices, which suggests that it may belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computer vision (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
